body:
I'm going to merge the changes in this pull request into a custom branch.
I'll open a new pull request (FLINK-1417) containing the commit from this PR.

@aljoscha: Can you close this PR?

I can confirm, the link is not removed in the clean phase. The maven junction plugin was last updated 5 years ago. Judging from the source at https://pyx4j.com/svn/pyx4j/pyx4j-maven-plugins/maven-junction-plugin everything should work fine.

However, I found what can be considered a bug. Before removing the link, the `JunctionUnlinkMojo` checks if the link exists:

```
if (link.getDst().exists()) { 
    // remove symlink
}
```

This returns false in our case because by the time this check is executed, `flink-dist/target/${project.version}-bin` has already been deleted. The symlink points to a non-existing directory. Instead of checking for the destination of the symlink, we need to check the actual symlinks existence.

Java 7's File has `isSymbolicLink`. For Java 6, something like http://stackoverflow.com/questions/813710/java-1-6-determine-symbolic-links/813730#813730 works.
